# Sega Design Standard

Use `docs/standards/sega.md` for Chackers branded game UI.

The Sega standard provides:

- Arcade-inspired visual direction.
- VT323-based typography guidance.
- Hard-edged components.
- Chunky game controls.
- Strong primary/secondary color tokens.
- Component states and accessibility expectations.

Do not apply Sega as random decoration. Apply it to product surfaces where a game identity helps:

- game board shell
- move controls
- timers
- mode selectors
- game status
- badges
- puzzle cards
- multiplayer room states

Keep Uncodixify active as the quality filter. If Sega styling becomes noisy, reduce the effect and preserve gameplay clarity.
